name: Indian ink
description:
Mixed-media, 4320 × 2788, 28 November 2019

When I found out that the studio I had been using for about 10 years was going to be demolished, I slapped Indian ink all over the walls of the studio a few months before I moved in. I took a photograph of one of the stains, which I intuitively chose while looking at the ink splatter, and digitally processed it afterwards for the record.
